# QuantumCue Cursor Rules

## Project Context

QuantumCue is a quantum computing marketplace and orchestration platform built with:
- Backend: Python 3.11+, FastAPI, SQLAlchemy 2.0+ (async), PostgreSQL
- Frontend: React 18, TypeScript 5.3+, Vite, TanStack Query, Zustand, Tailwind CSS, Recharts

## File Patterns

### Python Files
- Use type hints everywhere
- Async functions for database operations
- Google-style docstrings for public functions
- Follow repository -> service -> endpoint pattern

### TypeScript Files
- Use functional components with hooks
- Prefer named exports
- Use React Query for server state, Zustand for client state
- Follow component structure: imports, types, component, exports

## Code Completions

### When creating a new API endpoint:
1. Create Pydantic schemas in `backend/app/schemas/`
2. Create repository methods in `backend/app/repositories/`
3. Create service methods in `backend/app/services/`
4. Create endpoint in `backend/app/api/v1/endpoints/`
5. Add to router in `backend/app/api/v1/router.py`

### When creating a new React page:
1. Create page component in `frontend/src/pages/`
2. Create React Query hook in `frontend/src/hooks/`
3. Create API endpoint in `frontend/src/api/endpoints/`
4. Add route in `frontend/src/App.tsx`

### When creating a UI component:
1. Check if similar component exists in `frontend/src/components/ui/`
2. Use Tailwind classes matching design system colors (see Design System Colors section)
3. Accept className prop for customization
4. Include loading and error states
5. Support dark mode using `dark:` prefix classes

### When creating a chart component:
1. Use Recharts (NOT Chart.js - migrated in v2.0)
2. Import from `frontend/src/components/charts/` (ChartContainer, CustomTooltip, GradientDefs)
3. Use ChartContainer wrapper for consistent styling
4. Use CustomTooltip for branded tooltips
5. Include GradientDefs for quantum gradients
6. Add smooth animations (800ms duration, ease-out)
7. Use quantum color palette: purple (#a855f7), cyan (#06b6d4), green (#22c55e)

## Design System Colors (v2.0 - Light Theme Default)

### Primary Colors (Navy - Brand)
```
Navy 50-900:   Use navy-50 through navy-900
Primary Brand: navy-900 (#102a43) - Use for logo, primary buttons, headings
```

### Quantum Accent Colors
```
Quantum Purple: quantum-500 (#a855f7) - Primary quantum accent
Quantum Cyan:   cyan-500 (#06b6d4) - Jobs, providers, real-time data
Use quantum-50 through quantum-800 for full scale
Use cyan-50 through cyan-800 for full scale
```

### Semantic Colors
```
Success: success-500 (#22c55e) - Completed jobs, successful operations
Warning: warning-500 (#f59e0b) - Queued, processing
Error:   error-500 (#ef4444) - Failed jobs, validation errors
Info:    info-500 (#3b82f6) - General information
Use full scales (50, 100, 500, 600, 700) for backgrounds and text
```

### Neutral Greys (Cool-toned)
```
Grey 50-900:   Use grey-50 through grey-900
Background:    grey-50 (#f8fafc) - Primary background
Surface:       white - Card backgrounds
Text Primary: grey-700 (#334155) - Main text
Text Secondary: grey-500 (#64748b) - Secondary text
Text Tertiary: grey-400 (#94a3b8) - Placeholder, labels
```

### Dark Mode Support
- All components support dark mode via `dark:` prefix
- Use CSS variables for theme switching
- Theme managed by ThemeContext
- Default: light theme, dark mode optional toggle

### Tailwind Classes to Use
```
Backgrounds:  bg-white dark:bg-surface
              bg-grey-50 dark:bg-background
              bg-grey-100 dark:bg-surface-elevated

Borders:      border-grey-200 dark:border-border
              border-grey-300 dark:border-border-subtle

Text:         text-grey-900 dark:text-text-primary
              text-grey-600 dark:text-text-secondary
              text-grey-500 dark:text-text-tertiary

Buttons:      bg-gradient-primary (navy gradient)
              bg-gradient-quantum (purple to cyan)
              Use btn-primary, btn-quantum, btn-secondary, btn-ghost

Cards:        bg-white dark:bg-surface
              border border-grey-200 dark:border-border
              Use Card component with variant prop (default, elevated, stat)

Badges:       Use Badge component with variant prop
              (success, warning, error, info, quantum, default)
```

## Chart Library (Recharts)

### Usage Pattern
```typescript
import { BarChart, Bar, XAxis, YAxis, CartesianGrid, ResponsiveContainer, Tooltip } from 'recharts';
import { ChartContainer, CustomTooltip, GradientDefs } from '@/components/charts';

<ChartContainer title="Chart Title" height={400}>
  <ResponsiveContainer width="100%" height="100%">
    <BarChart data={data} margin={{ top: 20, right: 30, left: 20, bottom: 5 }}>
      <GradientDefs />
      <CartesianGrid strokeDasharray="3 3" stroke="#e2e8f0" className="dark:stroke-border" />
      <XAxis stroke="#64748b" className="dark:stroke-text-secondary" />
      <YAxis stroke="#64748b" className="dark:stroke-text-secondary" />
      <Tooltip content={<CustomTooltip />} />
      <Bar dataKey="value" fill="url(#barGradient)" radius={[8, 8, 0, 0]} animationDuration={800} />
    </BarChart>
  </ResponsiveContainer>
</ChartContainer>
```

### Available Gradients
- `url(#barGradient)` - Vertical gradient (purple to cyan)
- `url(#purpleGradient)` - Purple gradient
- `url(#cyanGradient)` - Cyan gradient
- `url(#quantumGradient)` - Horizontal gradient (purple to cyan)
- `url(#areaPurpleGradient)` - Area chart purple fill
- `url(#areaCyanGradient)` - Area chart cyan fill
- `url(#radialQuantumGradient)` - Radial gradient for circular charts

